1
00:00:43,920 --> 00:00:44,639
Miss Fan.

2
00:00:48,440 --> 00:00:49,519
I agree.

3
00:00:50,040 --> 00:00:51,079
Drink it while it's hot.

4
00:00:51,560 --> 00:00:52,799
What I mean is—

5
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:55,039
about the live-in marriage,

6
00:00:55,720 --> 00:00:56,799
I agree.

7
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:06,959
Good.

8
00:01:09,240 --> 00:01:11,039
After we are properly wed,

9
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:12,759
I'll tell everyone you married into my family.

10
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,079
Once the house is transferred to my name

11
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:16,599
and the finances are settled,

12
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:19,319
I'll find you the very best doctor in town,

13
00:01:19,360 --> 00:01:20,519
the best medicine to treat your wounds.

14
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:21,759
Once you've healed,

15
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:22,679
you may stay or go—

16
00:01:22,680 --> 00:01:23,519
whatever you wish.

17
00:01:23,520 --> 00:01:26,319
Aren't you worried that once I leave,

18
00:01:27,080 --> 00:01:28,959
your uncle will come back to seize the house?

19
00:01:32,240 --> 00:01:33,439
Once the house is officially transferred,

20
00:01:33,440 --> 00:01:34,439
what have I to fear from him?

21
00:01:36,160 --> 00:01:37,439
When you do leave,

22
00:01:37,520 --> 00:01:39,319
I'll just say you went away on business.

23
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:41,159
Who would know the difference?

24
00:01:42,760 --> 00:01:44,199
You've thought this through.

25
00:01:46,680 --> 00:01:47,679
If you stay,

26
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:49,479
I'll raise pigs and provide for you.

27
00:01:51,360 --> 00:01:52,199
Why?

28
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:53,799
You may not know,

29
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:56,599
but we pig butchers earn quite a good living.

30
00:01:58,480 --> 00:01:59,599
What I mean is—

31
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:02,639
if I became a burden,

32
00:02:03,160 --> 00:02:05,039
what would you get out of keeping me?

33
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:06,079
I get to look at a handsome face.

34
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:09,439
Fan Changyu!

35
00:02:09,920 --> 00:02:10,439
How can you say

36
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:12,359
something so honest?

37
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:15,759
There are so many

38
00:02:16,080 --> 00:02:18,039
handsome people in this world.

39
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:19,279
I know, but—

40
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:22,439
you're the one I carried out of the snow.

41
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:26,959
If you have nowhere to go after healing,

42
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:28,039
once healed,

43
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:29,879
I will take my leave.

44
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:32,399
I won't impose any further.

45
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:39,839
That's fine.

46
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:42,719
I'll head off then.

47
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:47,719
Miss Fan.

48
00:02:50,240 --> 00:02:51,319
For saving my life,

49
00:02:52,320 --> 00:02:53,319
I will repay you one day.

50
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:55,799
Is there anything you wish for?

51
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:57,639
Feel free to say.

52
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:01,719
There's nothing else I need.

53
00:03:02,920 --> 00:03:04,199
You're willing to pretend to marry into my family

54
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:05,559
and help me keep the house—

55
00:03:05,720 --> 00:03:06,839
that alone makes me grateful.

56
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:08,839
Pretending to be a live-in husband

57
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,199
is repayment enough for taking me in.

58
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:13,639
Is there a wish

59
00:03:13,920 --> 00:03:15,119
you want to dream bigger?

60
00:03:16,440 --> 00:03:18,199
A wish?

61
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:21,239
Dream bigger?

62
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:24,359
Then I'll think big.

63
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:27,079
I want to get my father's pig pens

64
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:28,399
up and running again.

65
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:30,439
Fence off a bigger plot of land,

66
00:03:31,040 --> 00:03:33,079
raise twenty or thirty pigs.

67
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:40,879
Think even bigger—

68
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:41,999
a hundred pigs.

69
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:45,119
What I mean is—

70
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:47,879
do you have any grand life ambitions?

71
00:03:48,080 --> 00:03:51,159
A hundred pigs would be worth over a hundred taels.

72
00:03:51,480 --> 00:03:53,119
That's not a grand life ambition?

73
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:56,959
Then two hundred.

74
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:58,239
I wouldn't be able to slaughter them all.

75
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:02,079
I understand.

76
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:06,639
Let's seal it with a handshake.

77
00:04:17,079 --> 00:04:18,199
Good day, Miss Changyu.

78
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:19,199
Good.

79
00:04:27,920 --> 00:04:32,919
Changyu, big sister!

80
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:34,039
Go play.

81
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:45,559
Good.

82
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:47,759
Thank you, Miss.

83
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:51,479
You're welcome.

84
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:53,999
Mistress Wang.

85
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:54,679
Changyu.

86
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:55,719
Sister Wang, Sister Zhang.

87
00:05:03,960 --> 00:05:04,719
Ladies.

88
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:07,439
My mother previously deposited fabric here

89
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:09,519
for me to have wedding clothes made.

90
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:11,799
Come this way.

91
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:12,239
Of course.

92
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:20,999
Yes, there is some fabric set aside—

93
00:05:21,080 --> 00:05:24,359
just enough to make one wedding outfit.

94
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:26,599
Can it be made into a man's wedding robe?

95
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:28,599
A man's wedding robe?

96
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:31,679
I knew that voice sounded familiar!

97
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:33,959
Isn't this our little Changyu?

98
00:05:33,960 --> 00:05:34,879
Auntie Chen!

99
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:36,519
I heard from Aunt Zhao

100
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:38,199
that you're getting married too.

101
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:40,439
When is the happy day?

102
00:05:42,320 --> 00:05:43,999
Getting the wedding clothes made now—

103
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,239
won't that be rushing it a bit?

104
00:05:45,640 --> 00:05:47,319
Ever since word got out about Chongzhou drafting soldiers,

105
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:49,479
everyone's rushing to marry,

106
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:51,639
wanting to leave an heir at home.

107
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:53,479
My helpers in the shop

108
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:54,479
can barely keep up.

109
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:58,879
I heard from Aunt Zhao

110
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:00,599
that the groom is quite handsome.

111
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,159
He's all right.

112
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:04,519
At least I'm not getting the short end.

113
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:07,639
Auntie Chen, please work quickly—

114
00:06:07,880 --> 00:06:09,319
I'll pay you extra.

115
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:11,079
Don't even talk about extra pay!

116
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:12,559
Don't you worry.

117
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:15,719
I helped your mother choose and set this fabric aside.

118
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:17,839
She so wanted to see you wed.

119
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:23,039
I heard from Aunt Zhao

120
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:26,559
that the groom is her distant relative from Chongzhou.

121
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:34,039
From Chongzhou?

122
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:37,719
Does he know whether Marquis Wu'an really died?

123
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:39,999
Marquis Wu'an is dead.

124
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:41,479
Really?

125
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,399
Marquis Wu'an—

126
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:45,159
Haven't you heard what everyone's saying outside?

127
00:06:45,160 --> 00:06:46,239
Marquis Wu'an is dead.

128
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:46,799
Died in Chongzhou.

129
00:06:46,960 --> 00:06:47,679
Not even a bone left.

130
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:48,679
Just like his father.

131
00:06:49,160 --> 00:06:49,999
Nonsense!

132
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,119
How could Marquis Wu'an die?

133
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:52,679
I'll smash that mouth of yours!

134
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:54,199
Everyone—should he be beaten?

135
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:09,959
We of Da Yin

136
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:12,599
have faced the Northern Di on the battlefield for many years.

137
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:16,039
Marquis Wu'an Xie Zheng—a hero of his generation—

138
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:17,959
has fallen without a body to bury.

139
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:19,999
This is a great sorrow for our nation.

140
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,119
We, Your Majesty,

141
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:25,159
wish to posthumously honor Xie Zheng as the Duke of Loyalty,

142
00:07:25,760 --> 00:07:27,919
and award his army one thousand gold taels.

143
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:31,559
What does the court say?

144
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:37,599
Your Majesty is most wise.

145
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:40,759
Marquis Wu'an defended our western borders

146
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:41,919
with unmatched valor.

147
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:43,999
In over a hundred years of our dynasty,

148
00:07:44,160 --> 00:07:46,079
this honor has been bestowed

149
00:07:46,520 --> 00:07:48,159
on only one man—Xie Zheng.

150
00:07:48,640 --> 00:07:51,319
To now confer upon him the title of Duke of Loyalty—

151
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:54,359
this truly reflects Your Majesty's virtue

152
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:56,479
and is a blessing for all people.

153
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:59,159
Marquis Wu'an rose to command armies at a young age

154
00:07:59,160 --> 00:08:01,999
and avenged the humiliation at Jinzhou.

155
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:05,159
The Northern Di trembled at his name.

156
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:07,759
All soldiers will shed their blood

157
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:09,839
to repay Your Majesty's grace.

158
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:11,159
I second the motion.

159
00:08:11,520 --> 00:08:13,679
Then let the imperial decree be issued.

160
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:15,279
We mourn deeply.

161
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:17,959
The court shall wear mourning attire.

162
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:20,839
The whole nation shall observe a period of mourning.

163
00:08:21,280 --> 00:08:23,679
We obey Your Majesty's decree.

164
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:26,559
Your Majesty, I arrived late—

165
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:53,519
The Chancellor has been unwell

166
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:55,119
yet still comes to court.

167
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:57,319
This is a blessing for Da Yin.

168
00:08:58,240 --> 00:08:59,039
Please be seated.

169
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,479
What have I missed?

170
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:14,159
We intend to honor Xie Zheng as the Duke of Loyalty,

171
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:16,439
award his army one thousand gold taels,

172
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:17,519
and order a national period of mourning.

173
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:21,359
What is the Chancellor's view?

174
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:25,359
Marquis Wu'an did earn great merit in battle,

175
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:28,919
but this concerns the situation at the front.

176
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:31,839
A national period of mourning

177
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:35,159
may affect the morale of our armies.

178
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:39,119
The Northern Di and Prince Changxin's forces

179
00:09:39,640 --> 00:09:41,799
would seize this opportunity.

180
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:50,319
With respect, Chancellor—

181
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:54,159
Marquis Wu'an gave his life for his nation in his prime.

182
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:57,319
His Majesty honors his early death out of compassion.

183
00:09:58,240 --> 00:10:00,799
This is a mark of imperial benevolence.

184
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:05,359
While scholars criticize his actions at Jinzhou,

185
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:06,799
his merits far outweigh his faults.

186
00:10:07,280 --> 00:10:09,039
When merit and fault are weighed,

187
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:11,239
merit wins without question.

188
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:14,439
His Majesty rewarding Marquis Wu'an now

189
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:16,479
is a clear and just act,

190
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:18,279
a measure to inspire all soldiers.

191
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:22,559
How could it harm morale?

192
00:10:24,640 --> 00:10:26,999
The Marquis's death has been reported,

193
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:29,359
yet no body has been found.

194
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:31,439
I chose not to report it publicly

195
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:33,719
to keep our enemies guessing.

196
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:37,079
As long as his death is not confirmed,

197
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:40,079
our enemies cannot be certain of our weakness

198
00:10:40,920 --> 00:10:42,759
and will not dare strike recklessly.

199
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:48,159
The Grand Tutor is skilled at reading the Emperor's mind,

200
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:51,319
but in matters of military strategy,

201
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:54,639
there is still much to learn.

202
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:07,879
The Chancellor speaks with great wisdom.

203
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:11,999
I have much to learn.

204
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:14,599
Chancellor.

205
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:22,959
Please accept my condolences.

206
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:25,639
Thank you for your kind words, Grand Tutor.

207
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:30,719
Now that Marquis Wu'an no longer guards Yanzhou,

208
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:33,319
who will

209
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:35,399
command the Yanzhou army?

210
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:42,039
The Yanzhou army is still Da Yin's army.

211
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:43,839
Any capable man at court

212
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,919
may be sent to Yanzhou.

213
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:49,919
The Yanzhou army is vital to border security.

214
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:51,919
We must proceed with the utmost care.

215
00:11:56,160 --> 00:11:58,439
If the Chancellor has a perfect plan,

216
00:11:58,440 --> 00:11:59,759
then I am the one who worried for nothing.

217
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,159
I'll take my leave.

218
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:14,919
That old fox, so concerned about the northwest—

219
00:12:14,920 --> 00:12:17,839
he must be plotting to gain control of the border forces.

220
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:24,639
Have Xie Zheng's remains been found?

221
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:25,639
Not yet.

222
00:12:28,160 --> 00:12:29,799
Has the eldest son reported anything

223
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:32,279
about the Marquis's disappearance?

224
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:33,759
Nothing.

225
00:12:34,520 --> 00:12:37,119
That day, they were too close to General He Jingyuan's territory.

226
00:12:37,960 --> 00:12:39,279
Fearing to alarm our quarry,

227
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:42,719
I've dispatched men to continue searching in secret.

228
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:44,199
Search harder.

229
00:12:44,760 --> 00:12:45,799
Tell them to be quick.

230
00:12:46,920 --> 00:12:49,639
Whether he lives or dies must be confirmed.

231
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:52,479
But more importantly, find that keepsake.

232
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:52,919
Yes.

233
00:12:53,160 --> 00:12:54,759
Tell the agents of the Xuan Division—

234
00:12:55,760 --> 00:12:56,599
if they fail to find it,

235
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:58,799
don't bother coming back.

236
00:12:58,800 --> 00:12:59,679
By your command.

237
00:14:34,080 --> 00:14:34,759
Get out of the way!

238
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:36,759
Get lost!

239
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:49,079
Move!

240
00:14:52,920 --> 00:14:53,999
Where did this wild wolf come from?

241
00:14:54,840 --> 00:14:56,239
My hair ribbon nearly got snatched.

242
00:15:00,720 --> 00:15:01,559
Where are my shoes?

243
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:33,999
This young lady truly isn't afraid of the cold—

244
00:15:34,720 --> 00:15:35,999
out in the snow,

245
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,679
walking barefoot on the road.

246
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:53,079
She must have met with some misfortune.

247
00:15:53,560 --> 00:15:54,759
Let's ask where she lives

248
00:15:54,760 --> 00:15:55,279
and give her a ride.

249
00:15:57,320 --> 00:15:58,159
Miss,

250
00:16:01,160 --> 00:16:03,479
my master takes pity on you

251
00:16:03,480 --> 00:16:04,359
walking in the snow.

252
00:16:04,680 --> 00:16:05,479
He offers to take you home. Where do you live?

253
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:08,399
No need, thank you.

254
00:16:11,760 --> 00:16:12,599
Miss, please wait.

255
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:26,079
My name is Li.

256
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:27,039
I mean no harm.

257
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:28,919
Walking barefoot in this weather—

258
00:16:28,920 --> 00:16:30,039
your feet will be ruined.

259
00:16:30,360 --> 00:16:31,439
Please allow me to take you.

260
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:37,759
Then thank you, sir.

261
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:48,399
Thank you, sir.

262
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:04,279
But you sitting outside—

263
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:06,399
I feel terrible about it.

264
00:17:07,040 --> 00:17:07,759
Think nothing of it.

265
00:17:08,079 --> 00:17:09,078
Your shoes and socks are soaked through.

266
00:17:09,079 --> 00:17:09,879
Warm your feet first.

267
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:12,119
I've been sitting inside the carriage too long—

268
00:17:12,120 --> 00:17:13,039
I needed some fresh air.

269
00:17:26,120 --> 00:17:28,519
Sister, you're back so soon!

270
00:17:28,880 --> 00:17:29,879
Changyu!

271
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:32,319
What happened to you?

272
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:35,279
A wild wolf chased me on the road.

273
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:36,599
I lost one shoe.

274
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:39,279
Thankfully these two gentlemen gave me a ride.

275
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:40,239
It was nothing.

276
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:42,799
Thank you both, sirs.

277
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:44,719
It's so cold out—

278
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:45,959
please come inside and warm up.

279
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:46,559
Aunt.

280
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:48,399
Let Miss Fan change her shoes first.

281
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:49,959
We have urgent matters

282
00:17:50,160 --> 00:17:51,159
and must be on our way.

283
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:52,999
Thank you, Mr. Li.

284
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:56,519
Sorry to trouble you.

285
00:17:57,520 --> 00:17:58,519
Please, gentlemen—wait.

286
00:17:58,680 --> 00:18:00,679
I just finished roasting some chestnuts.

287
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:02,239
Take some for the road.

288
00:18:02,240 --> 00:18:02,919
There's no need.

289
00:18:02,920 --> 00:18:05,439
My aunt's roasted chestnuts are delicious.

290
00:18:05,440 --> 00:18:06,559
They really are.

291
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:08,119
Take some and try.

292
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:09,279
Then we gratefully accept.

293
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:10,159
Thank you, kind Aunt.

294
00:18:10,720 --> 00:18:11,399
Just a moment.

295
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:12,079
Aunt.

296
00:18:14,840 --> 00:18:15,759
Why did you do that?

297
00:18:16,040 --> 00:18:17,319
The country folk show gratitude

298
00:18:17,320 --> 00:18:18,559
in simple, honest ways.

299
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:20,239
We need to blend in with the locals.

300
00:18:21,040 --> 00:18:22,519
It helps with the investigation.

301
00:18:22,880 --> 00:18:23,479
Right?

302
00:18:24,760 --> 00:18:26,639
Just admit you wanted the chestnuts.

303
00:18:45,080 --> 00:18:46,319
I saw nothing.

304
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:51,519
Come in.

305
00:18:58,240 --> 00:18:59,079
I—I—

306
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:03,119
I went to Auntie Chen's today to get the wedding clothes made,

307
00:19:03,120 --> 00:19:05,119
and I just realized I forgot to take your measurements.

308
00:19:07,680 --> 00:19:08,439
Come in.

309
00:19:34,360 --> 00:19:36,199
You look slender,

310
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:38,879
but your shoulders are quite broad.

311
00:19:39,960 --> 00:19:40,999
Like my father.

312
00:19:41,720 --> 00:19:42,879
Shoulder width: one foot eight.

313
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:58,359
Waist: two foot one.

314
00:20:01,080 --> 00:20:02,679
Inseam: three foot seven.

315
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:06,879
What's wrong?

316
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:08,919
Nothing.

317
00:20:09,240 --> 00:20:10,479
I was chased by a wolf this morning.

318
00:20:10,840 --> 00:20:11,879
I may have twisted my ankle.

319
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:14,559
Sit down—let me take a look.

320
00:20:14,560 --> 00:20:15,319
No need.

321
00:20:16,240 --> 00:20:17,959
Uncle Zhao will be back soon.

322
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:19,559
I'll just put some medicine on it.

323
00:20:25,560 --> 00:20:26,599
Sit down.

324
00:20:26,880 --> 00:20:27,639
Let me check.

325
00:20:27,840 --> 00:20:28,799
Don't let it hurt more tonight.

326
00:20:32,480 --> 00:20:33,479
[Advertisement]

327
00:20:33,480 --> 00:20:34,519
[Advertisement]

328
00:20:35,840 --> 00:20:37,199
[Advertisement]

329
00:20:37,560 --> 00:20:38,799
[Advertisement]

330
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:40,839
[Advertisement]

331
00:20:41,440 --> 00:20:42,439
[Advertisement]

332
00:20:42,440 --> 00:20:43,439
[Advertisement]

333
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:48,399
[Advertisement]

334
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:49,839
[Advertisement]

335
00:20:58,680 --> 00:21:00,279
Is it good?

336
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,239
For some reason,

337
00:21:09,880 --> 00:21:11,959
those mysterious men retreated after reaching Lin'an.

338
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:19,639
They vanished completely.

339
00:21:20,560 --> 00:21:21,239
Perhaps

340
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:23,599
I should ask the local magistrate.

341
00:21:25,640 --> 00:21:26,839
My mentor has instructed

342
00:21:27,320 --> 00:21:28,279
that this matter be kept private.

343
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:35,799
My Lord,

344
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:37,519
you've been riding all night

345
00:21:37,520 --> 00:21:38,799
searching for Marquis Wu'an

346
00:21:39,080 --> 00:21:40,359
with no result.

347
00:21:40,920 --> 00:21:41,879
I'd say

348
00:21:42,280 --> 00:21:43,359
in the chaos of battle,

349
00:21:43,560 --> 00:21:45,119
leaving no remains

350
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:46,519
is not uncommon.

351
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:47,999
I have a feeling

352
00:21:49,480 --> 00:21:51,199
Marquis Wu'an didn't die so easily.

353
00:21:54,080 --> 00:21:55,959
If those mysterious men still linger,

354
00:21:57,360 --> 00:21:59,159
the Marquis must be in Lin'an.

355
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:06,799
It's dislocated.

356
00:22:08,440 --> 00:22:09,239
Ow, ow, ow!

357
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:10,439
Of course it hurts—it was fully dislocated.

358
00:22:11,080 --> 00:22:13,079
I thought it was just a sprain.

359
00:22:14,280 --> 00:22:15,159
Bear with me.

360
00:22:19,720 --> 00:22:20,399
Done.

361
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:31,319
My Lord,

362
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:33,399
freshly roasted chestnuts—

363
00:22:33,400 --> 00:22:34,399
still hot.

364
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:35,359
Please, help yourself.

365
00:22:35,440 --> 00:22:36,239
Thank you, Aunt.

366
00:22:36,240 --> 00:22:36,759
Aunt,

367
00:22:37,840 --> 00:22:38,639
just now I heard

368
00:22:38,720 --> 00:22:40,239
Miss Fan calling from upstairs.

369
00:22:40,480 --> 00:22:41,359
Is everything all right?

370
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:44,399
That's Changyu's live-in husband.

371
00:22:44,840 --> 00:22:46,679
The young couple is probably just playing around.

372
00:22:46,960 --> 00:22:47,799
A husband?

373
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:51,879
Why didn't we see him come downstairs to greet Miss Fan?

374
00:22:52,640 --> 00:22:53,759
He has some injuries.

375
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:54,959
He can't easily come down.

376
00:22:57,160 --> 00:22:57,799
Tasty?

377
00:22:57,840 --> 00:22:59,039
Yes, yes, very tasty, Aunt.

378
00:22:59,800 --> 00:23:01,359
Now the northwest is at war.

379
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:02,879
I hear many wounded drifters

380
00:23:02,880 --> 00:23:04,639
from Chongzhou have come here,

381
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:06,439
trying to settle by getting married.

382
00:23:06,880 --> 00:23:07,959
The Fan girl's husband—

383
00:23:08,840 --> 00:23:10,159
he's not from Chongzhou too, is he?

384
00:23:14,440 --> 00:23:16,399
He's a distant relative of mine.

385
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:17,639
He came from Yanzhou.

386
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:26,279
It really doesn't hurt anymore.

387
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:28,039
Not even a little.

388
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,279
Told you not to wolf it down.

389
00:23:34,280 --> 00:23:34,839
Now you're paying for it.

390
00:23:35,560 --> 00:23:36,119
Aunt,

391
00:23:36,480 --> 00:23:37,719
may I trouble you for a cup of tea?

392
00:23:37,840 --> 00:23:38,719
Of course, of course!

393
00:23:39,520 --> 00:23:40,919
I was so busy getting you food,

394
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:41,719
I forgot about drinks.

395
00:23:42,640 --> 00:23:43,559
Please come in for some tea.

396
00:23:43,560 --> 00:23:43,919
Thank you.

397
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:52,679
Someone came downstairs?

398
00:23:53,720 --> 00:23:54,359
Oh no!

399
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:56,239
I completely forgot about our two guests downstairs!

400
00:24:01,840 --> 00:24:03,959
The tea isn't great—please forgive us.

401
00:24:04,720 --> 00:24:06,839
Miss Fan, you just got married?

402
00:24:09,960 --> 00:24:10,879
Actually,

403
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:13,079
he married into my household.

404
00:24:14,200 --> 00:24:14,959
A live-in husband.

405
00:24:16,280 --> 00:24:18,119
Poor soul.

406
00:24:18,360 --> 00:24:20,599
Just arrived in Lin'an from Yanzhou,

407
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:21,759
and ran into bandits.

408
00:24:21,760 --> 00:24:22,599
Robbed and wounded.

409
00:24:22,600 --> 00:24:23,679
Fortunately my Changyu took him in.

410
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:26,999
Changyu even slaughtered a pig

411
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:28,239
and sold it to pay for his treatment.

412
00:24:28,240 --> 00:24:29,599
Slaughtered a pig?

413
00:24:30,920 --> 00:24:31,719
My big sister is amazing—

414
00:24:34,120 --> 00:24:35,759
one slap and she can knock a pig out cold.

415
00:24:36,720 --> 00:24:38,559
She's joking.

416
00:24:39,840 --> 00:24:41,159
Miss Fan is most admirable.

417
00:24:46,480 --> 00:24:47,519
Most admirable indeed.

418
00:24:47,920 --> 00:24:48,919
Miss Fan, no need to see us out.

419
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:54,999
Take care.

420
00:24:56,120 --> 00:24:56,719
Walk safely.

421
00:24:58,320 --> 00:24:59,239
My Lord,

422
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:04,839
I think we're so obsessed with finding Marquis Wu'an

423
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:06,879
that we're imagining things.

424
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:07,959
Marquis Wu'an was someone who refused even a princess.

425
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:09,839
How could he possibly marry into a pig butcher's family

426
00:25:09,840 --> 00:25:10,719
and even massage her foot to set her ankle?

427
00:25:11,280 --> 00:25:13,239
I was overthinking it.

428
00:25:13,280 --> 00:25:14,879
You've gone several nights without sleep over this.

429
00:25:16,280 --> 00:25:17,359
Rest on the way back to Jizhou.

430
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:19,839
I'll handle things out here.

431
00:25:20,200 --> 00:25:21,999
Let's go.

432
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:23,319
Carriages from Jizhou.

433
00:25:24,840 --> 00:25:25,319
General He Jingyuan's men.

434
00:25:40,360 --> 00:25:41,759
What measurements did I take for Yan Zheng?

435
00:25:42,320 --> 00:25:43,639
Shoulder width—

436
00:25:50,320 --> 00:25:52,439
one foot eight.

437
00:26:02,280 --> 00:26:03,639
Waist—

438
00:26:06,880 --> 00:26:08,319
two foot one.

439
00:26:09,200 --> 00:26:12,319
Inseam—

440
00:26:14,520 --> 00:26:15,759
three foot seven.

441
00:26:16,800 --> 00:26:17,839
Yan Zheng.

442
00:26:28,840 --> 00:26:33,319
What is this?

443
00:26:59,840 --> 00:27:00,999
Could she have discovered something?

444
00:27:02,080 --> 00:27:03,679
Who is it?

445
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:16,279
It's me.

446
00:27:17,400 --> 00:27:18,199
I have something to say.

447
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:20,559
Come in.

448
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:24,799
I've already noted the measurements.

449
00:27:40,520 --> 00:27:42,399
I'll send them to the tailor shortly.

450
00:27:43,280 --> 00:27:44,279
Could you stay awake tonight?

451
00:27:56,640 --> 00:27:58,879
Wait until I come back.

452
00:27:59,520 --> 00:28:00,999
There's something I need us both to do.

453
00:28:04,600 --> 00:28:07,039
Just the two of us?

454
00:28:13,560 --> 00:28:14,839
You're a man; I'm a woman.

455
00:28:15,240 --> 00:28:16,399
I can't do it without you.

456
00:28:17,080 --> 00:28:18,559
That seems improper.

457
00:28:30,280 --> 00:28:31,839
You're about to become my live-in husband.

458
00:28:32,840 --> 00:28:33,919
What's improper about it?

459
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:35,159
It's settled. Not a word to Uncle and Aunt Zhao.

460
00:28:35,840 --> 00:28:36,679
Keep it secret.

461
00:28:47,200 --> 00:28:49,279
What do you need me to do?

462
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:50,119
Follow me—don't let anyone see.

463
00:29:32,640 --> 00:29:33,959
Kneel down.

464
00:29:34,200 --> 00:29:35,999
This is what you wanted

465
00:29:45,600 --> 00:29:46,279
the two of us to do together?

466
00:29:55,160 --> 00:29:56,759
My mother always said

467
00:29:57,720 --> 00:29:59,039
paying respects at night requires a man

468
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:02,599
with strong yang energy.

469
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:05,319
That's you.

470
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:07,799
So that's why she was writing

471
00:30:08,600 --> 00:30:09,279
in the dirt today.

472
00:30:24,160 --> 00:30:25,479
The magistrate hasn't issued an official death notice.

473
00:30:25,480 --> 00:30:27,559
Unofficial memorial rites could get us in trouble.

474
00:30:29,680 --> 00:30:31,399
The middle of the night when no one's around is best.

475
00:30:31,440 --> 00:30:33,679
Then whose memorial tablet is that?

476
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:36,079
When you were coughing blood badly,

477
00:30:37,040 --> 00:30:38,359
I thought you might not make it.

478
00:30:41,760 --> 00:30:43,679
So I carved one for you.

479
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:45,039
Thank you.

480
00:30:46,080 --> 00:30:46,959
No need—it wasn't used after all.

481
00:30:49,600 --> 00:30:50,479
Now that Marquis Wu'an has died in battle,

482
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:52,799
I wanted to give him a memorial tablet.

483
00:30:55,840 --> 00:30:57,559
As luck would have it,

484
00:30:58,520 --> 00:30:59,999
your name can be slightly changed to fit.

485
00:31:00,680 --> 00:31:01,639
Yes.

486
00:31:01,920 --> 00:31:03,839
Might as well put it to use.

487
00:31:05,280 --> 00:31:06,039
It's made of huang hua li wood.

488
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:08,079
Might as well use it.

489
00:31:09,720 --> 00:31:10,519
By the way—

490
00:31:10,920 --> 00:31:11,599
you escaped from Chongzhou.

491
00:31:13,640 --> 00:31:14,199
Do you know how the Marquis died?

492
00:31:14,520 --> 00:31:16,199
I don't know.

493
00:31:16,960 --> 00:31:18,839
You have no connection to him,

494
00:31:20,240 --> 00:31:20,839
so why pay your respects?

495
00:31:24,720 --> 00:31:26,479
Common gossip says

496
00:31:27,560 --> 00:31:28,799
that Marquis Wu'an was a bloodthirsty demon

497
00:31:29,960 --> 00:31:31,159
who slaughtered entire cities.

498
00:31:31,840 --> 00:31:33,559
Nonsense.

499
00:31:34,120 --> 00:31:35,479
My father said

500
00:31:36,240 --> 00:31:37,079
in over two hundred years of Da Yin,

501
00:31:38,440 --> 00:31:39,359
how many men like Marquis Wu'an were there?

502
00:31:40,200 --> 00:31:41,439
He reclaimed Jinzhou.

503
00:31:41,880 --> 00:31:43,759
Decades of fighting,

504
00:31:44,320 --> 00:31:45,359
losing countless great generals.

505
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:47,999
The twelve commanderies of Liaodong—

506
00:31:49,080 --> 00:31:50,279
he reclaimed those too.

507
00:31:51,320 --> 00:31:52,239
Today's scholars all despise that.

508
00:31:53,680 --> 00:31:54,919
Those so-called men of letters

509
00:32:03,720 --> 00:32:04,919
call him cold and brutal.

510
00:32:06,680 --> 00:32:08,719
But the soldiers and people who died at Jinzhou sixteen years ago—

511
00:32:08,720 --> 00:32:10,239
were they not innocent?

512
00:32:10,760 --> 00:32:12,399
General Xie stood tall and died with dignity,

513
00:32:13,360 --> 00:32:14,879
yet the Northern Di disemboweled him

514
00:32:16,880 --> 00:32:18,239
and displayed his body on the city wall.

515
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:20,839
He was the Marquis's own father.

516
00:32:20,840 --> 00:32:22,079
Avenging one's father is only right.

517
00:32:22,520 --> 00:32:23,799
Besides the Marquis,

518
00:32:25,200 --> 00:32:26,879
who else could guard the northwest?

519
00:32:28,800 --> 00:32:30,239
Why are you looking at me like that?

520
00:32:31,200 --> 00:32:32,439
Did I say something wrong?

521
00:32:33,000 --> 00:32:34,479
You're remarkably bold.

522
00:32:35,320 --> 00:32:36,519
There's no one else here.

523
00:32:37,200 --> 00:32:39,319
That's why I dare say it.

524
00:32:39,880 --> 00:32:41,159
Marquis Wu'an,

525
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:43,559
I, the commoner Fan Changyu,

526
00:32:43,560 --> 00:32:44,519
kneel here with my husband Yan Zheng

527
00:32:44,920 --> 00:32:46,799
to bid you farewell.

528
00:32:46,800 --> 00:32:48,159
May your spirit rest in peace.

529
00:32:48,160 --> 00:32:49,879
May your blessings protect the people of Da Yin.

530
00:32:53,720 --> 00:32:55,839
If you meet my parents in the afterlife,

531
00:32:56,480 --> 00:32:57,599
please give them my regards.

532
00:32:58,200 --> 00:32:59,239
Is there anything you wish to say?

533
00:32:59,960 --> 00:33:01,639
Kneel and speak it.

534
00:33:06,400 --> 00:33:07,919
Marquis Wu'an gave his life for his country.

535
00:33:08,360 --> 00:33:09,359
He is worthy of this bow.

536
00:33:11,920 --> 00:33:13,119
May the fog of deception lift.

537
00:33:17,600 --> 00:33:18,759
May the truth

538
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:20,039
be revealed to the world.

539
00:33:32,040 --> 00:33:33,039
Big sister.

540
00:33:33,880 --> 00:33:35,119
Your braid is crooked.

541
00:33:35,920 --> 00:33:37,159
Come here, let me see.

542
00:33:37,160 --> 00:33:38,239
It doesn't look crooked.

543
00:33:42,120 --> 00:33:43,439
Make do for today.

544
00:33:44,120 --> 00:33:46,679
When I've sold the pork,

545
00:33:48,720 --> 00:33:50,279
I'll buy you some candy.

546
00:33:53,760 --> 00:33:55,319
Go get dressed.

547
00:34:06,160 --> 00:34:07,319
Good morning, Changyu!

548
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:09,519
Morning, Changyu!

549
00:34:12,080 --> 00:34:13,599
Good morning, Miss!

550
00:34:14,240 --> 00:34:15,719
Morning!

551
00:34:39,720 --> 00:34:41,879
Changyu!

552
00:34:43,440 --> 00:34:44,719
Morning!

553
00:34:46,159 --> 00:34:47,759
Morning, Changyu!

554
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:34,959
Morning!

555
00:35:36,520 --> 00:35:38,279
Morning, Changyu, dear!

556
00:35:38,560 --> 00:35:39,759
Morning!

557
00:35:41,120 --> 00:35:42,439
Changyu, dear,

558
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:47,599
are you giving away the braised pig hearts today?

559
00:35:51,040 --> 00:35:52,199
Not today.

560
00:35:54,720 --> 00:35:56,199
The braised hearts are for sale.

561
00:35:56,200 --> 00:35:57,319
I only gave them away on opening day.

562
00:35:57,320 --> 00:35:58,599
From now on, they're sold.

563
00:35:59,840 --> 00:36:00,599
Thirty coins per jin.

564
00:36:12,440 --> 00:36:13,199
But other butchers include offal for free

565
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:14,959
when you buy meat.

566
00:36:14,960 --> 00:36:16,119
Which shop?

567
00:36:17,840 --> 00:36:18,799
Master Guo's—

568
00:36:19,160 --> 00:36:20,799
buy meat, get free offal.

569
00:36:21,800 --> 00:36:22,119
Come on over!

570
00:36:22,120 --> 00:36:22,359
Are you doing the same?

571
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:23,359
If not, I'll go to his shop.

572
00:36:23,720 --> 00:36:24,599
Of course I am!

573
00:36:38,600 --> 00:36:39,519
Good, then I won't go.

574
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:41,799
Weigh me two jin of shoulder pork.

575
00:36:42,960 --> 00:36:43,919
Here you are, Aunt Tao.

576
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:45,599
And here's your braised heart. Take it.

577
00:36:46,040 --> 00:36:47,759
Right then.

578
00:36:47,880 --> 00:36:49,079
Here you go, miss.

579
00:36:49,560 --> 00:36:50,879
Your meat.

580
00:36:50,920 --> 00:36:52,439
That Master Guo—

581
00:36:53,800 --> 00:36:56,999
he stopped you from giving away extras,

582
00:36:57,160 --> 00:36:58,759
then started doing it himself.

583
00:36:59,200 --> 00:37:00,079
He has a cousin who clerks at the magistrate's office.

584
00:37:01,400 --> 00:37:02,439
Watch out.

585
00:37:02,720 --> 00:37:06,199
Understood.

586
00:37:09,480 --> 00:37:10,119
Look at this meat.

587
00:37:10,240 --> 00:37:11,959
Still better to buy from Fan's.

588
00:37:12,920 --> 00:37:13,999
The lean cuts are a deeper red,

589
00:37:14,360 --> 00:37:16,399
and the braised flavors are richer.

590
00:37:18,440 --> 00:37:19,719
Not like over there—pale as dead pig meat.

591
00:37:20,560 --> 00:37:21,959
What's that about?

592
00:37:21,960 --> 00:37:23,319
I bet their braised sauce is made with real gold water.

593
00:37:26,440 --> 00:37:27,799
Good thing you're back—

594
00:37:29,280 --> 00:37:30,919
let's see how long that free offal routine lasts.

595
00:37:30,920 --> 00:37:31,559
Talking about me, are you?

596
00:37:36,800 --> 00:37:37,879
We'll see who lasts.

597
00:37:38,240 --> 00:37:38,919
Yin Niang, my noodles?

598
00:37:39,960 --> 00:37:41,759
So impatient!

599
00:37:41,880 --> 00:37:43,159
You'd think I was starving you.

600
00:37:43,400 --> 00:37:44,879
Coming right up.

601
00:37:46,120 --> 00:37:48,239
I'm just hungry!

602
00:37:48,240 --> 00:37:49,319
Hurry up.

603
00:37:50,640 --> 00:37:51,119
Changyu—

604
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:52,399
I'll head off now.

605
00:37:52,400 --> 00:37:53,719
If that Guo fellow gives you trouble again,

606
00:37:53,720 --> 00:37:54,839
just tell me.

607
00:37:54,960 --> 00:37:55,719
I'm not afraid of him.

608
00:37:56,040 --> 00:37:57,439
See you!

609
00:37:57,760 --> 00:37:59,799
How many jin?

610
00:38:00,480 --> 00:38:02,439
Two jin will do.

611
00:38:03,480 --> 00:38:04,879
Two jin it is—make it two for me as well.

612
00:38:06,680 --> 00:38:09,239
Foolish bird.

613
00:38:09,720 --> 00:38:11,319
Falling for such an obvious trap.

614
00:38:12,520 --> 00:38:13,999
Come up.

615
00:38:15,720 --> 00:38:18,039
Go on.

616
00:38:19,160 --> 00:38:21,199
Already at Lin'an's Four Seasons Bookshop.

617
00:38:21,680 --> 00:38:22,559
Hurry.

618
00:38:22,560 --> 00:38:23,519
While that girl is away,

619
00:38:23,560 --> 00:38:24,399
search quickly.

620
00:38:24,400 --> 00:38:25,239
You two—check outside.

621
00:38:26,480 --> 00:38:27,119
I'll go upstairs.

622
00:38:28,040 --> 00:38:28,719
Back courtyard: clear.

623
00:38:28,720 --> 00:38:29,719
Kitchen: empty.

624
00:38:29,960 --> 00:38:31,559
Upstairs: nobody.

625
00:38:31,560 --> 00:38:32,479
We shouldn't cause extra trouble now.

626
00:38:32,720 --> 00:38:34,639
Besides, there's nothing valuable in here.

627
00:38:36,080 --> 00:38:36,799
Listen—

628
00:38:37,600 --> 00:38:38,559
if we don't find the deed this time,

629
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:39,759
we lose our jobs.

630
00:38:39,800 --> 00:38:40,999
Search properly.

631
00:39:18,160 --> 00:39:18,919
Fine.

632
00:39:19,280 --> 00:39:20,999
Uncle Wang looks busy today.

633
00:39:31,040 --> 00:39:31,679
I won't trouble you further.

634
00:39:43,560 --> 00:39:44,079
About the property transfer—

635
00:39:51,840 --> 00:39:54,639
Say no more.

636
00:40:02,640 --> 00:40:03,239
Fan Da

637
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:05,119
has already filed his complaint.

638
00:40:05,120 --> 00:40:06,279
The hearing will be within ten days.

639
00:40:06,280 --> 00:40:07,319
Be ready.

640
00:40:07,440 --> 00:40:08,599
One more thing—

641
00:40:09,520 --> 00:40:10,599
on my wedding day,

642
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:16,879
please come early for the celebration.

643
00:40:23,160 --> 00:40:24,359
Of course, my girl.

644
00:40:29,160 --> 00:40:30,519
You're quick!

645
00:40:39,880 --> 00:40:41,679
Congratulations in advance.

646
00:40:42,200 --> 00:40:44,599
I'll definitely be there.

647
00:40:44,600 --> 00:40:45,479
One more thing to ask of you.

648
00:40:45,840 --> 00:40:47,439
My husband's money and travel papers

649
00:40:47,560 --> 00:40:48,879
were taken by bandits.

650
00:40:49,160 --> 00:40:50,119
He's about to register as my live-in husband.

651
00:40:50,640 --> 00:40:51,559
Could I apply for replacement papers?

652
00:41:03,800 --> 00:41:05,479
With all the crackdowns on drifters right now,

653
00:41:05,520 --> 00:41:07,159
getting replacement papers

654
00:41:07,600 --> 00:41:10,159
is not easy.

655
00:41:10,440 --> 00:41:11,399
But your father once did me a great kindness.

656
00:41:12,080 --> 00:41:12,959
I'll take care of this for you.

657
00:41:13,120 --> 00:41:14,639
Thank you, Uncle Wang.

658
00:41:15,080 --> 00:41:16,679
Fortunate to have you here.

659
00:41:16,680 --> 00:41:18,159
Don't mention it.

660
00:41:21,080 --> 00:41:22,199
Just consider it a wedding gift.

661
00:41:22,720 --> 00:41:23,959
Look at this carefully.

662
00:41:24,720 --> 00:41:26,239
Found it!

663
00:41:27,320 --> 00:41:28,759
Come, look!

664
00:41:29,040 --> 00:41:30,279
See—

665
00:41:30,880 --> 00:41:31,919
that wretched girl.

666
00:41:32,280 --> 00:41:33,319
Hid it behind the grain jars.

667
00:41:34,520 --> 00:41:36,279
What a search.

668
00:41:36,960 --> 00:41:39,199
Finally found it.

669
00:41:39,520 --> 00:41:41,039
Stop right there.

670
00:41:41,400 --> 00:41:43,039
Wait—there's someone in here?

671
00:41:43,240 --> 00:41:44,799
How did you all miss him?

672
00:41:45,920 --> 00:41:47,999
Put the deed down

673
00:41:48,040 --> 00:41:49,079
What?

674
00:41:49,080 --> 00:41:50,399
I said—

675
00:41:51,160 --> 00:41:52,799
put the deed down

676
00:41:53,200 --> 00:41:54,759
and I'll let you go.

677
00:41:56,040 --> 00:41:57,039
A three-legged man

678
00:41:57,320 --> 00:41:59,079
thinks he's tough?

679
00:41:59,160 --> 00:41:59,839
A cripple—

680
00:42:00,200 --> 00:42:01,519
can't even stand up straight,

681
00:42:04,240 --> 00:42:05,639
and you want to fight?

682
00:42:32,600 --> 00:42:33,039
Think I can't break that one good leg of yours?

683
00:42:34,400 --> 00:42:39,239
Try me.

684
00:42:39,680 --> 00:42:40,079
See—

685
00:42:40,840 --> 00:42:41,759
that wretched girl,

686
00:42:41,760 --> 00:42:43,239
hid it behind the grain jars.

687
00:42:43,240 --> 00:42:44,839
What a search.

688
00:42:46,960 --> 00:42:47,999
Finally found it.

689
00:42:50,160 --> 00:42:50,879
Stop right there.

690
00:42:57,480 --> 00:42:58,559
Wait—there's someone in here?

691
00:42:58,600 --> 00:43:00,439
How did you all miss him?

692
00:43:06,080 --> 00:43:07,399
Put the deed down—

693
00:43:08,800 --> 00:43:09,479
What?

694
00:43:09,840 --> 00:43:10,999
I said—

695
00:43:11,640 --> 00:43:13,279
leave the deed,

696
00:43:14,240 --> 00:43:15,719
and I'll let you go.

697
00:43:18,560 --> 00:43:19,559
A three-legged man

698
00:43:19,600 --> 00:43:20,679
thinks he's so tough?

699
00:43:20,720 --> 00:43:22,359
A cripple—

700
00:43:22,560 --> 00:43:23,679
you can barely even stand,

701
00:43:24,120 --> 00:43:25,279
and you want to fight?

702
00:43:25,920 --> 00:43:27,039
Think I can't break that one good leg of yours?

703
00:43:28,280 --> 00:43:30,719
You're a cripple!

704
00:43:31,160 --> 00:43:32,119
Try me.
